        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 14. Antianthe group and Tropidarnis II: A, Antianthe expansa (Germar), male style from posterior aspect,  09 - 183 a 3: 1, style clasp from posterior aspect angled laterally. B, Tropidarnis tectigera Fowler, male style from posterior aspect,  72 - 10 g 3: 1, style clasp from posterior aspect vertical. C, A. expansa, aedeagus from lateral aspect,  09 - 183 a 3. D, Tropidarnis tectigera, aedeagus from lateral aspect,  72 - 10 g 3. E, A. expansa, connective from dorsal aspect  09 - 183 a 3. F, A. expansa, female second valvulae from lateral aspect,  09 - 183 bƤ: 1, second valvulae with middle and apical large teeth distinctly closer; 2, second valvulae basal teeth. a, aedeagus. c, style clasp. cn, connective." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/205233/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.205222>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic relationships generated from cladistic analysis of the entire dataset, illustrating the new proposed reclassification of the Smiliini s. l. Analysis in PAUP * resulted in a single most parsimonious tree with 311 steps. Bremer support and synapomorphies for nodes are listed in Table 6." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/205222/files/figure.png" .

